{"info": {"author": "Jonatan Almen", "author_email": "almen.jonatan@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "### OddsPortal scraper \n\n```python\nfrom scrapers.odds_scraper import start\n\nstart(\"https://www.oddsportal.com/soccer/england/premier-league/\", path=\"datafile.csv\")\n```\n\n#### Run: \n\nSince we are \"tabbing\" the windows it will switch focus to the browser, running it within a virtual framebuffer \nis preferable if you do not run it on a dedicated server.  \n\n```.env\n$ xvfb-run python main.py\n```\n\nFor testing purposes one can run the script as is and watch the browser switch tabs.\n\n### Requirements\n\nchromedriver for your version of google chrome must be in your PATH\n\nXvfb if you're going running within virtual buffer\n\nhttps://chromedriver.chromium.org/\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/almenjonatan/bookie_scrapers", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "bookie-scraper", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bookie-scraper/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bookie-scraper/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/almenjonatan/bookie_scrapers"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/bookie-scraper/0.4.0/", "requires_dist": ["selenium", "attr"], "requires_python": ">=3.8", "summary": "Oddsportal Web Scraper", "version": "0.4.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h3>OddsPortal scraper</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">scrapers.odds_scraper</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">start</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"https://www.oddsportal.com/soccer/england/premier-league/\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">path</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s2\">\"datafile.csv\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h4>Run:</h4>\n<p>Since we are \"tabbing\" the windows it will switch focus to the browser, running it within a virtual framebuffer\nis preferable if you do not run it on a dedicated server.</p>\n<pre>$ xvfb-run python main.py\n</pre>\n<p>For testing purposes one can run the script as is and watch the browser switch tabs.</p>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<p>chromedriver for your version of google chrome must be in your PATH</p>\n<p>Xvfb if you're going running within virtual buffer</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://chromedriver.chromium.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://chromedriver.chromium.org/</a></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6869608, "releases": {"0.4.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "163c8903dd3dcf58a1104f1b97ca4610", "sha256": "faa6b7828374a18bd39dcaad3e1f3941b6ada853116c0ab172189e19dc7e6ce0"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "bookie_scraper-0.4.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "163c8903dd3dcf58a1104f1b97ca4610", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.8", "size": 7134, "upload_time": "2020-03-24T00:16:14", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-24T00:16:14.216825Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/11/50/eacf40e68b738b05512660e34101e30360e6daec9564686d720a43f8f584/bookie_scraper-0.4.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "bb4950a5e7608fecaf5aaef11f44701d", "sha256": "cd564c244370f1679dc819b6b067d395fe77b667f2de1ad993bae20a7cfa9eff"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "bookie-scraper-0.4.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "bb4950a5e7608fecaf5aaef11f44701d", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.8", "size": 4955, "upload_time": "2020-03-24T00:16:16", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-24T00:16:16.120405Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/25/9b/e2